        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "It depends on your original contract with the developer. Most off-the-plan contracts in Queensland restrict assignment or nomination of the contract to a third party and require the developer's written consent. Some contracts prohibit resale before settlement entirely. You need to read your contract carefully or have your solicitor review it before making any commitments to sell. If the contract allows assignment with consent, there is a process to follow, but it typically involves legal costs for both parties and the developer charging an assignment fee."
      }
